> This Cheeseburger Style Beef Rice Bowl is a crowd pleaser and is one to get the family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily customised to suit the kids too.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} using a #garlic press{}. Pop a #deep saucepan{} with a tight-fitting lid on medium heat. Melt in the @butter{10%g}. When hot, add half the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%min}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} until coated, ~{1%min}.

Add @salt{1/4%tsp} and the @water for the rice{300%ml} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

In the meantime, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{10-12%mins}.

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice. Set aside for later.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, olive oil for the dressing and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Stir in the tomatoes and set aside to macerate.

Once the onions are golden, add the remaining @sugar{1%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%mins} more. Transfer to a #small bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and return to medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the beef is browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Add the remaining @garlic clove{1} and fry for ~{1%min}.

Add the @beef stock paste{10%g}, @water for the sauce{100%ml} and @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} to the pan, then stir until combined.

Cook until the beef is glazed and the sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%mins}, then remove from the heat.

Once everything's cooked, add the baby gem to the tomato bowl and toss to coat.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between your #bowls{}.

Spoon the beef over one half of the rice and add the salad to the remaining half. Top with the caramelised onions.

Sprinkle the cheese and drizzle the @burger sauce{45%g} over the beef to finish.

Enjoy!